    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Introduction of CSS</title>
    <style>
        Body {
            background-color: blue;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">

    </div>
    <!--Explanination ..
    CSS is sort form of Cascading Style Sheet and it's used to make your website 
    beauty and attractive-->
    <!--We need to open style and container tag to write CSS -->
    <!--Points to remember:-->
    <!--We should open style tag after the title-->
    <!--we should open div container tag after main body tag-->
</body>

</html>
